cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource allocation and optimization in cognitive radio networks, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves maximizing the sum rate of secondary users in cognitive radio networks, which is a problem related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the time slot structures of secondary users in cognitive radio networks, which is a problem related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses optimizing the throughput of real-time and non-real-time secondary users in cognitive radio networks, which is a problem related to multimedia. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves formulating a mixed integer nonlinear programming task, which is a problem related to game theory.
